  "name": "Rageshkor shield, rock",
  "type": "shield",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Vesk have used rageshkor frill plates for shields since ancient times. In the post-Gap era, vesk have developed high-tech versions of these shields that incorporate synthetic padding, alloyed fittings, and more to augment the natural materials while maintaining the shields&rsquo; cultural value. Although these shields can be purchased, a carrier in vesk territory should expect to be asked whether the shield was truly won (harvested from a rageshkor the wielder defeated), where the clash occurred, and how the battle fared. An earned rageshkor shield is a prestige piece that can win a warrior much respect.</p>\n<h3>Rock Rageshkor Shield</h3>\n<p>This roughly ovular shield is made of big rock rageshkor frill plates. The shield can be used to make unarmed attacks that don&rsquo;t count as archaic. It also functions as if it had a mk 1 thermal capacitor installed, and this &ldquo;upgrade&rdquo; can be enhanced to higher model numbers without occupying the shield&rsquo;s other upgrade slot.</p>",
